5. Cosmological Architecture: The Resonant Celestial Engine
The theory's predictive power culminates in a new model for black holes, re-envisioned as Resonant Celestial Engines.
Theorem 5.1 (Tri-Phasic Black Hole Structure): A gravitationally collapsed object is a symbiotic system of the three Epsilonium phases:
Core (Base Epsilonium): A central information crystal that encodes the complete history of infalling matter, resolving the Information Paradox.
Halo (Modulus Epsilonium): A power-generating layer of resonant fire, where gravitational potential is converted into coherent radiation organized into golden-ratio spirals.
Ring (Tension Epsilonium): A topological processor at the center, stabilized by the halo's frame-dragging, forming a stable, traversable gateway.
